NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, should I have tried for slam? First of all, let's discuss how good slam is. You have two potential spade losers, and one potential heart loser. Basically, the hand is on two of three finesses. Now, most of you might assume that the odds of two of three finesses working is less than 50%. But, actually, it is exactly 50%. The combinations are all finesses lose, two finesses lose, one finesse loses, or no finesses lose. So, in two out of four cases (one finesse loses or no finesse loses) the contract makes. Hence, the odds are 50% that you will win two of three finesses. It is  counter intuitive, but true.|
