^-|HT|f|CP||FP|1|at|^B@2^Z@3B|FP||AT|ridge information stays with me as long as writing on the sand at the beach. It takes only one soft wave to wash everything away. However, as I get older I become more persistent and keep writing on the sand--reviewing the material over and over. However, for this week I like to bring you a good read. It is the "Fore-Word" for ^*IWhy You Lose At Bridge Table^*N by S. S. Simon. Charles Goren wrote it in March 1, 1946 and I only bring you the last section where he is quoting from the book. The book is a great read any many teachers recommend it. Please enjoy it.|
